Timetable of Class Meetings

Note on updates to the Timetable -- It is important to check the Timetable, rather than the ORC to confirm the latest information about a course, including the meeting time, instructor, and distributive and/or world culture designation associated with a course.

 

The distributive column on the Timetable is important since it contains the most up-to-date information on the distributive and/or world culture designation for the course. In some cases, the instructor has submitted a request to the Committee on Instruction for a change or addition in the distributive or world culture designation for a course since the ORC was published.

 

Click on the subject code link below to view ORC(Organization, Regulation and Course) information for that subject.

 

To view textbook requirements information as entered by the department/program at the time of course election, click on the course title.
Please check with the department/program for any updates.
